  <description type="morphology">Stems 3–8 cm; cortical cells small, walls thick; pseudoparaphyllia few; rhizoids few, in clusters just below leaf insertion, smooth. Leaves crowded, upturned-homomallous particularly near branch ends, scarcely altered on drying, concave, 1–2 × 0.5–0.8 mm; alar cells enlarged, yellow-brown, walls thick, region in several rows of cells, concave; basal laminal cell walls pitted; medial cells linear, 55–95 × 5–8 µm, walls moderately thick. Seta 1.5–3.2 cm, flexuose. Capsule reddish orange-brown, 1.7–3 mm, slightly wrinkled when dry; endostome segments not or narrowly perforated along keel. Spores 10–18 µm, yellow.</description>
